    "narrative": "For the April 16th slate, the heart of our lineup features high-leverage production from **Yordan Alvarez** (65.44) and **Junior Caminero** (59.77), both of whom benefit significantly from prime top-of-the-order placement. **Yordan Alvarez** remains our most consistent offensive engine; his favorable matchup against Mejia provides a clear path to high-value counting stats. Meanwhile, **Junior Caminero** faces Leasure in a matchup where the Zebras are betting on volume over high-end efficiency; while Leasure\u2019s 3.44 xERA is a hurdle, **Junior Caminero**'s elite bat-to-ball skills in the two-hole make him an essential anchor for our 5x5 Roto output. **Gary Sanchez** (58.68) also provides strong utility value today, capitalizing on a platoon advantage against Corbin that pushes his efficiency well above his baseline expectations.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench centered on **Josh Smith**, whose score of 39.60 fell just short of our strict 40.0 floor. Despite a favorable +10% park factor, a significant -15% drag caused by his platoon disadvantage against the lefty Lopez, combined with an unfavorable spot in the eight-hole, forced our hand. Elsewhere, the roster continues to navigate availability hurdles, with **Christian Yelich** remaining on the IL and both **Pete Crow-Armstrong** and **Kyle Schwarber** missing the slate due to team off-days. We remain particularly vigilant regarding **Dillon Dingler** (55.99); while he slots in as a solid start against Bubic, our internal model penalizes him slightly for the low SB upside presented by the opposing arm, though his projected clean-up role provides enough floor to keep him firmly in the C2 slot.",
